Name: HubSpot CRM Companies
Description: Work with companies in the HubSpot CRM
Share Context: HubSpot CRM Context from ./tool.gpt
Tools: Create Company,  Get Company, Delete Company, Update Company, Search Companies
Tools: ./associations.gpt, ./properties.gpt, ./owners.gpt
Params: prompt: detailed request to be executed against the HubSpot API


Fulfill the users request: ${PROMPT}

Use the tools available to you.

---
Name: Create Company
Description: Creates a new company/lead in the HubSpot CRM
Credential: ./credential
Params: properties: a json object with all the properties of the company

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/createCompany.py

---
Name: Get Company
Description: Retrieves a company by ID from the HubSpot CRM
Credential: ./credential
Params: company_id: the ID of the company to retrieve

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/getCompany.py

---
Name: Delete Company
Description: Deletes a company by ID from the HubSpot CRM
Credential: ./credential
Params: company_id: the ID of the company to delete

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/deleteCompany.py

---
Name: Update Company
Description: Updates an existing company in the HubSpot CRM by ID
Credential: ./credential
Params: company_id: the ID of the company to update
Params: properties: a json object with all the properties of the company

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/updateCompany.py

---
Name: Search Companies
Description: Searches for companies in the HubSpot CRM
Credential: ./credential
Params: filters: a json object with one or more keys in the format `{"<PROPERTY_NAME>":"<VALUE_TO_SEARCH_FOR>"}`. Each key in the json must be a valid property name returned by the 'HubSpot CRM Get Properties' tool.

#!/usr/bin/env python3 ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/searchCompanies.py
